{% paidFeature feature="paid_subscriptions" /%}

You can charge your readers for access to premium content on your newsletter. Paid subscriptions are set up with the following steps:

1. Sign up for [Stripe](https://stripe.com) (which takes your customers' money & sends it to you) and connect it to Buttondown.
2. Create a paid plan with the pricing & terms that best suit you.
3. Promote your paid plan to subscribers.
4. Send paid-exclusive emails to your paid subscribers.

In this guide, you'll learn how to get set up with paid subscribers, collect your first paying readers, and send your first paywalled email to them.

## Setup

First, go to [Stripe](https://stripe.com) and register for a new account.

Then, go to [Settings → Basics](https://demo.buttondown.com/settings/general). Under "Features", you'll see "Paid subscriptions". Tap "Connect to Stripe" at right. You'll be sent to Stripe to log in & connect your account to your newsletter.

### A note on Stripe's test mode

After you've [integrated](/stripe) your Buttondown and Stripe accounts, you can configure your paid subscription plan in Buttondown.

Buttondown does not currently support Stripe's [test mode](https://stripe.com/docs/test-mode), which lets you test your integration without charging a credit card.

To test your integration, we recommend charging a small amount on a real credit card and then refunding the charge. This will cost a few cents for each transaction.

### Using payment processors other than Stripe

Buttondown only supports Stripe natively right now. If you'd like to provide additional payment options for your subscribers, we recommend integrating creator platform tools like [Memberful](https://buttondown.com/features/integrations/memberful), [Zapier](https://zapier.com/apps/patreon/integrations/buttondown), or Patreon with Buttondown.

## Configuring paid plans

Once you've connected Stripe to Buttondown, go to [Settings → Integrations → Stripe](https://buttondown.com/settings/paid-subscriptions) to begin configuring your paid plans.

1. Navigate to [Settings](https://buttondown.com/settings/general) and scroll to the "Paid subscriptions" section.
1. Click **Configure**. The "Paid subscriptions" page appears.
1. Configure your subscription settings using the form:
   - **Content access**: Choose who can subscribe to your newsletter (no paid subscriptions, free & paid subscriptions, or paid only)
   - **Product**: Select which Stripe product to use (if you have multiple)
   - **Currency**: Choose the currency for your subscription plan
   - **Payment model**: Select Fixed, Pay what you want, or Per email
   - **Cadence**: Choose Monthly or Yearly billing
   - **Price**: Set the subscription price (for fixed pricing models)
   - **Yearly upsell price**: Optionally set a discounted yearly price (when monthly is selected)
   - **Embedded checkout**: Choose whether to show the payment element immediately on the subscribe page
1. Click **Save** to apply your changes.

