### Taxes

Stripe automatically reports and collects taxes for your paid newsletter. You can learn more about this on our [Stripe setup page](/stripe), or by reading [Stripe's documentation](https://stripe.com/docs/tax/set-up).

You may also need to register your paid newsletter with your local tax authority. Stripe has a tool to help you determine if you need to do this. You can use this tool in the "Monitoring" tab of your tax "Overview" page. If Stripe advises you to register with your local tax authority, Stripe's [Registration](https://stripe.com/docs/tax/registering#add-a-registration) guide explains the process of adding, editing, and checking the status of your registration. To learn more, read [Stripe's tax monitoring documentation](https://stripe.com/docs/tax/monitoring).
